<div class="prose-content max-w-3xl">

  <div class="bg-brand-light rounded-lg p-4 mb-6 text-sm">
    <strong>Please allow 2 working days</strong> for your prescription to be processed before collecting from the pharmacy.
  </div>

  <h2>Option 1 — Patient Access (online)</h2>
  <p>The easiest way to order repeat prescriptions is through Patient Access, available 24 hours a day.</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Log in to <a href="{{ site.patientAccess }}" rel="noopener noreferrer">Patient Access</a>.</li>
    <li>Go to "Prescriptions" and select the items you need.</li>
    <li>Submit your request. You'll receive a confirmation.</li>
    <li>Your prescription will be sent to your chosen pharmacy once processed.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>Not registered with Patient Access? <a href="{{ site.patientAccess }}" rel="noopener noreferrer">Register here</a> — you'll need your NHS number and a form of ID.</p>

  <h2>Option 2 — By email</h2>
  <p>Email your repeat prescription request to <a href="mailto:{{ site.prescriptionEmail }}">{{ site.prescriptionEmail }}</a>. Please include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Your full name and date of birth</li>
    <li>The name and dosage of each medication you need</li>
    <li>Your preferred pharmacy for collection</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Option 3 — Via your pharmacy</h2>
  <p>Many local pharmacies can request your repeat prescription on your behalf. Ask at your pharmacy whether they offer this service.</p>

  <h2>Option 4 — Prescription drop-box</h2>
  <p>You can post your repeat prescription slip in the prescription drop-box at Leven Health Centre reception. Please write your preferred pharmacy on the slip.</p>

  <h2>Nominating a pharmacy</h2>
  <p>If you'd like your prescription sent directly to a pharmacy, you can nominate a pharmacy through Patient Access, or ask our reception team to update your record.</p>

  <h2>Prescription policies</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>We do not accept prescription requests by telephone.</strong> Please use one of the four methods above.</li>
    <li><strong>Travelling abroad?</strong> If you are going abroad for three months or more, we can supply up to three months of your repeat medication before you leave. Patients who remain abroad longer than three months may be removed from our list and should register with a GP in the country they are living in.</li>
    <li><strong>Diazepam and flight anxiety.</strong> We are unable to prescribe diazepam or other benzodiazepines to manage anxiety about flying. If you have concerns about flying, please speak to your pharmacist about suitable alternatives, or discuss anxiety management with your GP at a routine appointment.</li>
  </ul>

</div>
